misuse

名词读作 ˌmɪsˈjuːs ，动词读作 ˌmɪsˈjuːz 。 

1. N-VAR The misuse of something is incorrect, careless, or dishonest use of it. 误用; 滥用 

例： ...the misuse of power and privilege. …权力和特权的滥用。 

2. V-T If someone misuses something, they use it incorrectly, carelessly, or dishonestly. 误用; 滥用 

例： She misused her position in the appointment of 26,000 party supporters to government jobs. 她滥用职权任命了26000名党派支持者从事政府工作。 

例： Tess would like a dollar for every time she had heard that word misused by television journalists. 特丝每次听到电视台记者用错那个词，都恨不得收他们一美元。

